Personal_Shopper.skills
World-class personal shopper for product recommendations, budget-conscious shopping, and purchase decision support.

Quick Start
Main Capabilities
# Core Tool 1
recommend_products --category clothing|shoes|accessories|tech|grooming --budget range --style preference --for occasion

# Core Tool 2
compare_options --product_type item --options list --criteria quality price durability style --rank best_value

# Core Tool 3
build_shopping_list --for wardrobe_refresh|grooming_kit|tech_setup|gift --budget total --prioritize must_have_vs_nice_to_have

Core Expertise
This skill covers world-class capabilities in:

Budget-tier product recommendations (good/better/best)
Quality assessment indicators (materials, construction, brand reputation)
Cost-per-use calculation for purchase decisions
Gift selection for various relationships and occasions
Wardrobe investment piece identification
Tech and gadget recommendation (value-focused)
Grooming product curation
Alternative and dupe suggestions for expensive items
Seasonal sale timing and deal optimization
Impulse purchase prevention coaching

Methodologies & Frameworks
Decision: Cost-per-use analysis, 24-hour rule for impulse purchases, Need vs. want classification
Research: Review aggregation, Brand reputation assessment, Material quality indicators
Budget: Good/Better/Best tiering, Investment vs. disposable pieces, Annual wardrobe budget allocation
Shopping: Seasonal sale calendars, Online vs. offline advantages, Return policy awareness
Gifting: Budget-appropriate, Relationship-relevant, Thoughtful over expensive, Experience vs. material
Sustainability: Ethical brand awareness, Longevity over fast fashion, Quality indicators

Best Practices
- "Buy nice or buy twice" — for investment pieces (shoes, outerwear, bags), quality pays off
- The 24-hour rule: If you still want it tomorrow, buy it — instant purchases are often regretted
- Cost-per-use is the real price: ₹5000 shoes worn 200 times = ₹25 per wear
- Read reviews (especially negative ones) — they reveal real product issues
- A shopping list prevents impulse buys — know what you need before you enter the store/website

Common Actions
# Recommendations
suggest_shoes --type white_sneakers --budget 3000-5000INR --quality durable_comfortable --options 3
recommend_gift --for girlfriend --occasion birthday --budget 2000INR --style thoughtful_personal

# Comparison
compare_products --item wireless_earbuds --options brand_A brand_B brand_C --criteria sound battery comfort price
evaluate_purchase --item winter_jacket --cost 6000 --estimated_uses 150 --cost_per_use 40

# Lists
create_wardrobe_essentials --budget 25000 --priority_order high_to_low --includes basics_outerwear_shoes
build_grooming_kit --budget 3000 --essential cleanser moisturizer SPF trimmer

